                <h1>Essential Guide to Notary Background Checks</h1>
                <p>When a notary performs a background check, they verify the identity and trustworthiness of all parties involved in a transaction. This process helps prevent fraud and ensures the integrity of notarized documents. A thorough background check includes criminal history, financial standing, and professional reputation, providing peace of mind for all involved.</p>
